Interface ITypeInfoDTO

public interface ITypeInfoDTO

Method Detail

getName

java.lang.String getName()
Get the name of the type. For a Jazz item, the name is the component's namespace URI, followed by a ".", and then the simple name of the type (e.g. "com.ibm.team.repository.Contributor").

Returns:
the name of a type supported by a manager; never null or empty

setName

void setName(java.lang.String value)
Set the name of the supported type. For a Jazz item, the name must be in the format described in ITypeInfoDTO.getName().

Parameters:
value - the name of a type supported by a manager; must not be null or empty

getMappedName

java.lang.String getMappedName()
Get the name of the type that can be mapped to this type, if known. This can be used to indicate which type "on the other side" can be mapped to this type. For example, for an external type that represents a user identity, this value could be set to "com.ibm.team.repository.Contributor" to indicate that the external type can be mapped to a Jazz user identity.

Returns:
the name of the type that this type can be mapped to if known; may be null or empty
Since:
0.7

setMappedName

void setMappedName(java.lang.String value)
Set the name of the type that this type can be mapped to.

Parameters:
value - the name of the type that this type can be mapped to; may be null or empty
Since:
0.7

getQualifierId

java.lang.String getQualifierId()
Get any qualifier for this type. A qualifier can be thought of as a "sub-type", and represents a value that can be used in the ISyncRule.SYNC_ITEM_TYPE_QUALIFIER_PROPERTY of a synchronization rule.

Returns:
a qualifier for, or sub-type of, this type; may be null or empty

setQualifierId

void setQualifierId(java.lang.String value)
Set the qualifier for this type.

Parameters:
value - a qualifier identifying a "sub-type" of this type; may be null or empty
See Also:
ITypeInfoDTO.getQualifierId()

getQualifierName

java.lang.String getQualifierName()
Get the "friendly" name for the type qualifier, if it has one. If there is a type qualifier and it has a friendly name, it will be displayed in the sync rule editor, but the ID will still be entered into the sync rule itself.

Returns:
any friendly name for a type qualifier; may be null or empty

setQualifierName

void setQualifierName(java.lang.String value)
Set any "friendly" name for the type qualifier.

Parameters:
value - the friendly name of the type qualifier; may be null or empty
See Also:
ITypeInfoDTO.getQualifierName()

isSyncAllStates

boolean isSyncAllStates()
Determine whether all states of this type of object must be synchronized, as opposed to just the latest state. All states should be synchronized if there are constraints on the states of an object (e.g. a work flow that must be followed, such as for a work item).

Returns:
true if all states should be synchronized; false if only the latest state need be synchronized

setSyncAllStates

void setSyncAllStates(boolean value)
Set whether all states of this type of object must be synchronized.

Parameters:
value - true to synchronize all state; false to only synchronize the latest state

getProperties

java.util.List getProperties()
Get information about the properties supported for this type. To add property information, add elements to the list returned by this method.

Returns:
information about supported propeties; never null; may be empty
